Description: Papyrus written with black ink with demotic legal text on recto (remains of 4 ll.) and verso (originally it had probably names of 8 witnesses). Verso has a black stamp. Thompson's MS Catalogue: "A contract of which only the protocol remains, the substantive part being lost. Date. year 47 Tybi (?) of Ptol. Euergetes II = BC. 123 Jan-Feb. (prob.). Origin. Memphis. Cf. no. 10393".

Martin 2016 / Tree Papyri: Two Frames (no 2, p. 83-87.)
